THE ALEX JONES SHOW 
2010.03.16 Tuesday

Alex talks with film and video director, producer, and musician Kevin Booth. Booth's film, American Drug War - The Last White Hope, has won three consecutive awards for &quot;Best Feature Length Documentary&quot; and was featured on Showtime. In his latest film, How Weed Won the West, Booth traces the fight against Federal drug regulation in the State of California. He interviews radio host Alex Jones, former drug dealers, real-life gang members, legal-weed pitch men, activists and advocates to find the truth. Alex also talks with author, historian, and journalist Webster Tarpley. Tarpley is the author of 9/11 Synthetic Terror: Made in USA, Obama - The Postmodern Coup: Making of a Manchurian Candidate, Surviving the Cataclysm: Your Guide through the Worst Financial Crisis in Human History, and Barack H. Obama: The Unauthorized Biography. Alex also covers the news and takes your calls.

HOUR 1: News, Moody's to drop U.S./U.K. AAA ratings?, War with IRan?,
Pentagon targets WIKILEAKS and the Web itself, anyone critical of Government
is a &quot;terrorist&quot; - where's the fourth amendment?, American Takeover, wake up
to the Invisible Empire, double dip recession - it's a Depression folks, 
U.S. dollar in free fall, who owns American debt?, public land is already
under U.N. and UNESCO Treaty courtesy of George W. Bush, FEMA camps and census
tracking, etc.

HOUR 2: Don't drink the water, Open Lines, climate change - it's colder because
it is hotter?, school spying and induction into police state grid, etc.

HOUR 3: Open Lines, KEVIN BOOTH, government drug dealing, the world's poppy fields
are in Afghanistan folks, drug war - war on America?, etc.

HOUR 4: WEBSTER GRIFFIN TARPLEY, signs: coming government attack on the Internet,
now the Internet is defined as a weapon system, end of the &quot;free Internet&quot;?, Tax on
Banks (will ultimately be tax on clients), policy of austerity, banking 
parasites destroying industrialized society, Tarpley calls for Tobin tax,
Tax speculation (flash trading, derivitives, etc.) - not regressive taxation
like food tax, etc. 

88.7 FM Olympia, WA (west side)
